    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed the required level. The single deficiency (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is mitigated by the use of two independent laboratories and the deterministic nature of the F1717 test protocol. All quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96, percentage difference < 10%) are satisfied for all three QoIs. The overall credibility evidence is judged sufficient to support a Medium assurance level conclusion for the non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending COU.",
